From: Ajith <ajith@example.com>
Date: Sat, 27 Jun 2026 23:11:00 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] Forward SUSFS supercall magic to susfs_handle_sys_reboot()

KPROBES_HOOK mode registers a kprobe on __arm64_sys_reboot to intercept
the reboot syscall for KSU operations (KSU_INSTALL_MAGIC1 = 0xDEADBEEF).
However, SUSFS uses 0xFAFAFAFA as its magic value, which was being
silently dropped — the kprobe fired but ksu_handle_sys_reboot() returned
immediately because magic1 didn't match the KSU magic.

Add a check for SUSFS magic1 (0xFAFAFAFA) and forward the call to
susfs_handle_sys_reboot() via its extern declaration. This allows
SUSFS operations from userspace tools (brene, ksu_susfs tool) to work
correctly under KPROBES_HOOK mode.

The extern declaration is resolved at link time against our compat
shim in drivers/kernelsu/susfs_compat.c.

Signed-off-by: Ajith <ajith@example.com>
---
 kernel/supercall/supercall.c | 9 ++++++++-
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/KernelSU-Next/kernel/supercall/supercall.c b/KernelSU-Next/kernel/supercall/supercall.c
index e8c0e37..c1cad43 100644
--- a/KernelSU-Next/kernel/supercall/supercall.c
+++ b/KernelSU-Next/kernel/supercall/supercall.c
@@ -26,6 +26,9 @@

 #include "tiny_sulog.h"

+/* Forward declaration — resolves to susfs_handle_sys_reboot() in compat shim */
+extern int susfs_handle_sys_reboot(unsigned int cmd, void __user *arg);
+
 static int do_grant_root(void __user *arg)
 {
 	// we already check uid above on allowed_for_su()
@@ -71,8 +74,16 @@ int ksu_handle_sys_reboot(int magic1, int magic2, unsigned int cmd,
 			  void __user **arg)
 {
-	if (magic1 != KSU_INSTALL_MAGIC1)
+	if (magic1 != KSU_INSTALL_MAGIC1) {
+		/* SUSFS communication protocol: userspace calls
+		 * reboot(0xFAFAFAFA, 0, cmd, arg) to trigger SUSFS operations.
+		 * Route via our compat shim's susfs_handle_sys_reboot().
+		 */
+		if (magic1 == 0xFAFAFAFA) {
+			return susfs_handle_sys_reboot(cmd, *arg);
+		}
 		return 0;
+	}

 #ifdef CONFIG_KSU_DEBUG
 	pr_info("sys_reboot: intercepted call! magic: 0x%x id: %d\n", magic1,
